### Student Record Management API - Live Demonstration
### Install the "REST Client" extension in VS Code to click and run these requests directly.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 1. CHECK SERVER & DATABASE STATUS
### -------------------------------------------------------------
GET http://localhost:3000/status

###

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 2. TEST INPUT VALIDATIONS (EXPECTING 400 BAD REQUEST)
### -------------------------------------------------------------

# A. Try to register a student with an invalid email format
POST {{baseUrl}}/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "email": "invalid-email-format",
  "date_of_birth": "2000-01-01"
}

###

# B. Try to register a student with an invalid date format
POST {{baseUrl}}/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "John",
  "last_name": "Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "01-01-2000"
}

###

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 3. REGISTER STUDENTS (EXPECTING 201 CREATED)
### -------------------------------------------------------------

# A. Register Student A (Alice)
POST {{baseUrl}}/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Alice",
  "last_name": "Smith",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "2002-05-14"
}

###

# B. Register Student B (Bob)
POST {{baseUrl}}/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Bob",
  "last_name": "Jones",
  "email": "bob@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "2001-08-22"
}

###

# C. Try to register a duplicate email (Expect 400 Bad Request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/students
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "first_name": "Duplicate",
  "last_name": "Alice",
  "email": "alice@example.com",
  "date_of_birth": "2000-01-01"
}

###

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 4. SEARCH, SORT, AND PAGINATION
### -------------------------------------------------------------

# A. Search for students named "Alice"
GET {{baseUrl}}/students?search=Alice

###

# B. Sort students by first_name in descending order (Bob should appear first)
GET {{baseUrl}}/students?sortBy=first_name&order=DESC

###

# C. Get paginated students list (Limit = 1, Page = 2)
GET {{baseUrl}}/students?limit=1&page=2

###

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 5. CREATE COURSES (EXPECTING 201 CREATED)
### -------------------------------------------------------------

# A. Create Course A (CS-101)
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_code": "CS-101",
  "title": "Introduction to Computer Science",
  "credits": 3,
  "description": "Fundamental programming concepts"
}

###

# B. Create Course B (CS-102)
POST {{baseUrl}}/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "course_code": "CS-102",
  "title": "Data Structures & Algorithms",
  "credits": 4,
  "description": "Arrays, Trees, Graphs, Sorting algorithms"
}

###

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 6. ENROLL STUDENTS IN COURSES
### -------------------------------------------------------------

# A. Enroll Alice (ID 1) in CS-101 (ID 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student_id": 1,
  "course_id": 1
}

###

# B. Enroll Alice (ID 1) in CS-102 (ID 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student_id": 1,
  "course_id": 2
}

###

# C. Enroll Bob (ID 2) in CS-101 (ID 1)
POST {{baseUrl}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student_id": 2,
  "course_id": 1
}

###

# D. Try duplicate enrollment (Alice in CS-101 again) -> (Expect 400 Bad Request)
POST {{baseUrl}}/enrollments
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "student_id": 1,
  "course_id": 1
}

###

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 7. MANAGE GRADES
### -------------------------------------------------------------

# A. Update Alice's grade in CS-101 to 'A+' (Enrollment ID is 1)
PUT {{baseUrl}}/enrollments/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "grade": "A+"
}

###

# B. Get Alice's (ID 1) enrolled courses (Should show CS-101 with grade A+ and CS-102 with null grade)
GET {{baseUrl}}/students/1/courses

###

### -------------------------------------------------------------
### 8. CASCADE DELETION TEST (RELATIONAL INTEGRITY)
### -------------------------------------------------------------

# Step A: Check students currently enrolled in CS-101 (Expect Alice and Bob)
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/1/students

###

# Step B: Delete Alice (ID 1)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/students/1

###

# Step C: Verify Alice's profile returns 404 Not Found
GET {{baseUrl}}/students/1

###

# Step D: Re-check CS-101 enrolled students (Expect ONLY Bob to be enrolled)
# This proves SQLite CASCADE DELETE deleted Alice's enrollment automatically!
GET {{baseUrl}}/courses/1/students
